#: ../../../cmds/fish_should_add_to_history.rst:2
msgid ""
"fish_should_add_to_history - decide whether a command should be added to the "
"history"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_should_add_to_history.rst:5
msgid "Synopsis"
msgstr "概要"

#: ../../../cmds/fish_should_add_to_history.rst:7
msgid "fish_should_add_to_history"
msgstr "fish_should_add_to_history"

#: ../../../cmds/fish_should_add_to_history.rst:13
msgid ""
"function fish_should_add_to_history\n"
"    ...\n"
"end"
msgstr ""
"function fish_should_add_to_history\n"
"    ...\n"
"end"

#: ../../../cmds/fish_should_add_to_history.rst:19
msgid "Description"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_should_add_to_history.rst:21
msgid ""
"The ``fish_should_add_to_history`` function is executed before fish adds a "
"command to history, and its return status decides whether that is done."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_should_add_to_history.rst:23
msgid ""
"If it returns 0, the command is stored in history, when it returns anything "
"else, it is not. In the latter case the command can still be recalled for "
"one command."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_should_add_to_history.rst:25
msgid ""
"The first argument to ``fish_should_add_to_history`` is the commandline. "
"History is added *before* a command is run, so e.g. :envvar:`status` can't "
"be checked. This is so commands that don't finish like :doc:`exec` and long-"
"running commands are available in new sessions immediately."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_should_add_to_history.rst:27
msgid ""
"If ``fish_should_add_to_history`` doesn't exist, fish will save a command to "
"history unless it starts with a space. If it does exist, this function takes "
"over all of the duties, so commands starting with space are saved unless "
"``fish_should_add_to_history`` says otherwise."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_should_add_to_history.rst:30
msgid "Example"
msgstr "範例"

#: ../../../cmds/fish_should_add_to_history.rst:32
msgid "A simple example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_should_add_to_history.rst:36
msgid ""
"function fish_should_add_to_history\n"
"    for cmd in vault mysql ls\n"
"         string match -qr \"^$cmd\" -- $argv; and return 1\n"
"    end\n"
"    return 0\n"
"end"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_should_add_to_history.rst:43
msgid ""
"This refuses to store any immediate \"vault\", \"mysql\" or \"ls\" calls. "
"Commands starting with space would be stored."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_should_add_to_history.rst:47
msgid ""
"function fish_should_add_to_history\n"
"    # I don't want `git pull`s in my history when I'm in a specific "
"repository\n"
"    if string match -qr '^git pull' -- \"$argv\"\n"
"    and string match -qr \"^/home/me/my-secret-project/\" -- (pwd -P)\n"
"        return 1\n"
"    end\n"
"\n"
"    return 0\n"
"end"
msgstr ""
